This rule checks for consistent capitalization of generic names in entity declarations.

**Violation**

```vhdl
entity FIFO is
  generic (
    G_WIDTH : natural := 16
  );
  port (
    I_DATA : std_logic_vector(g_width - 1 downto 0);
    O_DATA : std_logic_vector(g_width - 1 downto 0)
  );
end entity fifo;
```

**Fix**

```vhdl
entity FIFO is
  generic (
    G_WIDTH : natural := 16
  );
  port (
    I_DATA : std_logic_vector(G_WIDTH - 1 downto 0);
    O_DATA : std_logic_vector(G_WIDTH - 1 downto 0)
  );
end entity fifo;
```

